{
  "texts": [
    "Referral data from primary care practitioners to teledermatology consultations were used to train a model capable of a top-3 accuracy and specificity of 93 and 83%, respectively, given 26 skin conditions that makeup 80% of encountered primary care cases (4).",
    "This performance was on par with dermatologists and surpassed primary care physicians (PCPs) and nurse practitioners.",
    "This type of model could assist PCPs in diagnosing patients more accurately and broadening their differential diagnoses.",
    "In cases in which the top 3 diagnoses from the model have the same management strategy, patients may start treatment while awaiting further workup or follow-up with dermatology.",
    "Nevertheless, further testing on populations with a low prevalence of skin cancer is essential to demonstrate efficacy in the broader population (23)."
  ]
}